1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,440
Keeping a Smartsheet program tracker current is usually a manual chore.

2
00:00:04,740 --> 00:00:12,957
Here is a tool that does it for you, from the validated SAS or R you already run on a schedule, with no A-I and no copy and paste.

3
00:00:13,257 --> 00:00:17,735
This is a representative demo of the C-P one-oh-one program tracker.

4
00:00:18,035 --> 00:00:20,815
Click run, and watch a single night's job.

5
00:00:21,815 --> 00:00:23,128
One scheduled run.

6
00:00:23,428 --> 00:00:30,939
The job reads the sheet, computes tonight's operational status, and writes it back to each row by a stable key.

7
00:00:31,239 --> 00:00:44,209
Enrollment drops to At Risk; the database cut moves to Watch and its date slips; the spec ticks up to eighty-five percent; and one genuinely new row is appended, all in a single idempotent upsert.

8
00:00:45,209 --> 00:00:51,759
Look at the log on the right: real reads and writes to the Smartsheet A-P-I, then the status attachment.

9
00:00:52,059 --> 00:01:00,989
And the instant the status cell changed to At Risk, Smartsheet's own workflow, the one a project manager configured once, emailed them.

10
00:01:01,289 --> 00:01:05,050
The code wrote the fact; Smartsheet decided who to tell.

11
00:01:06,050 --> 00:01:07,990
Run the very same job again.

12
00:01:08,290 --> 00:01:15,514
Nothing duplicates, because every row is matched by its key, so it reports rows updated and zero added.

13
00:01:15,814 --> 00:01:21,040
Re-running is always safe; the sheet just converges to the same truthful state.

14
00:01:22,040 --> 00:01:25,270
And the safety boundary is in code, not policy.

15
00:01:25,570 --> 00:01:37,587
When a non-operational column tries to ride along, the ops-only allowlist blocks it and the job stops, so no participant-level data and no reported clinical number can ever reach the cloud.

16
00:01:38,587 --> 00:01:39,895
That is the whole idea.

17
00:01:40,195 --> 00:01:49,367
Your tracker is always current, the alerts are automatic, and you never paste a status again, all from validated SAS and R you already own.

18
00:01:49,667 --> 00:01:56,551
The library ships ready to use: drop in your sheet, your key, and your allowlist, and schedule it.
